The Ondo State Police Command, on Monday, confirmed that the commercial driver, Felix Akinde, abducted by kidnappers along Ado Ekiti/ Akure road has regained his freedom. See Kidnappers Demand N5m To Free Driver Abducted In Ondo The State Police Public Relations Officer, Mr Femi Joseph, who confirmed this to Nigerian Tribune said the Akinde was released last weekend. Joseph who said the Command will soon invite the released victim to interrogate him in order to investigate the incident, vowing that the criminals would be brought to book soon. Tribune